					<div id=3D"mw-content-text" class=3D"mw-body-content"><div class=3D"mw=
-content-ltr mw-parser-output" lang=3D"en" dir=3D"ltr"><div class=3D"shortd=
escription nomobile noexcerpt noprint searchaux" style=3D"display:none">Rat=
io of two numbers</div>
<div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">For other us=
es, see <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fraction_(disambiguation)"=
 class=3D"mw-disambig" title=3D"Fraction (disambiguation)">Fraction (disamb=
iguation)</a>.</div>
<p class=3D"mw-empty-elt">
</p>
<figure class=3D"mw-default-size" typeof=3D"mw:File/Thumb"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Cake_quarters.svg" class=3D"mw-file-descripti=
on"><img src=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b9/C=
ake_quarters.svg/250px-Cake_quarters.svg.png" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"2=
50" height=3D"190" class=3D"mw-file-element" data-file-width=3D"504" data-f=
ile-height=3D"383"></a><figcaption>A cake with one quarter (one fourth) rem=
oved. The remaining three fourths are shown by dotted lines and labeled by =
the <span class=3D"nowrap">fraction <span class=3D"frac"><span class=3D"num=
">1</span>=E2=81=84<span class=3D"den">4</span></span></span>.</figcaption>=
</figure>
<p>A <b>fraction</b> (from <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Latin_l=
anguage" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Latin language">Latin</a>: <i lang=
=3D"la">fractus</i>, "broken") represents a part of a whole or, more genera=
lly, any number of equal parts. When spoken in everyday English, a fraction=
 describes how many parts of a certain size there are, for example, one-hal=
f, eight-fifths, three-quarters. A <i>common</i>, <i>vulgar</i>,<sup id=3D"=
cite_ref-vulgar_1-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/Fraction#cite_note-vulgar-1"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>n =
1<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> or <i>simple</i> fraction =
(examples: <span class=3D"sfrac">=E2=81=A0<span class=3D"tion"><span class=
=3D"num">1</span><span class=3D"sr-only">/</span><span class=3D"den">2</spa=
n></span>=E2=81=A0</span> and <link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" hr=
ef=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1214402035"><span class=3D"sfrac">=E2=81=A0<s=
pan class=3D"tion"><span class=3D"num">17</span><span class=3D"sr-only">/</=
span><span class=3D"den">3</span></span>=E2=81=A0</span>) consists of an in=
teger <b>numerator</b>, displayed above a line (or before a slash like <lin=
k rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1154=
941027"><span class=3D"frac"><span class=3D"num">1</span>=E2=81=84<span cla=
ss=3D"den">2</span></span>), and a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/Division_by_zero" title=3D"Division by zero">non-zero</a> integer <b>denom=
inator</b>, displayed below (or after) that line. If these integers are pos=
itive, then the numerator represents a number of equal parts, and the denom=
inator indicates how many of those parts make up a unit or a whole. For exa=
mple, in the fraction <link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw=
-data:TemplateStyles:r1214402035"><span class=3D"sfrac">=E2=81=A0<span clas=
s=3D"tion"><span class=3D"num">3</span><span class=3D"sr-only">/</span><spa=
n class=3D"den">4</span></span>=E2=81=A0</span>, the numerator 3 indicates =
that the fraction represents 3 equal parts, and the denominator 4 indicates=
 that 4 parts make up a whole. The picture to the right illustrates <link r=
el=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1214402=
035"><span class=3D"sfrac">=E2=81=A0<span class=3D"tion"><span class=3D"num=
">3</span><span class=3D"sr-only">/</span><span class=3D"den">4</span></spa=
n>=E2=81=A0</span> of a cake.
</p><p>Fractions can be used to represent <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/Ratio" title=3D"Ratio">ratios</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Division_(mathematics)" title=3D"Division (mathematics)">divisi=
on</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-2" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/Fraction#cite_note-2"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>=
1<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Thus the fraction <link re=
l=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r12144020=
35"><span class=3D"sfrac">=E2=81=A0<span class=3D"tion"><span class=3D"num"=
>3</span><span class=3D"sr-only">/</span><span class=3D"den">4</span></span=
>=E2=81=A0</span> can be used to represent the ratio 3:4 (the ratio of the =
part to the whole), and the division <span class=3D"nowrap">3 =C3=B7 4</spa=
n> (three divided by four).
</p><p>We can also write negative fractions, which represent the opposite o=
f a positive fraction. For example, if <link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-=
style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1214402035"><span class=3D"sfrac">=
=E2=81=A0<span class=3D"tion"><span class=3D"num">1</span><span class=3D"sr=
-only">/</span><span class=3D"den">2</span></span>=E2=81=A0</span> represen=
ts a half-dollar profit, then =E2=88=92<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-=
style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1214402035"><span class=3D"sfrac">=
=E2=81=A0<span class=3D"tion"><span class=3D"num">1</span><span class=3D"sr=
-only">/</span><span class=3D"den">2</span></span>=E2=81=A0</span> represen=
ts a half-dollar loss. Because of the rules of division of signed numbers (=
which states in part that negative divided by positive is negative), =E2=88=
=92<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyle=
s:r1214402035"><span class=3D"sfrac">=E2=81=A0<span class=3D"tion"><span cl=
ass=3D"num">1</span><span class=3D"sr-only">/</span><span class=3D"den">2</=
span></span>=E2=81=A0</span>, <link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" hr=
ef=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1214402035"><span class=3D"sfrac">=E2=81=A0<s=
pan class=3D"tion"><span class=3D"num">=E2=88=921</span><span class=3D"sr-o=
nly">/</span><span class=3D"den">2</span></span>=E2=81=A0</span> and <link =
rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r121440=
2035"><span class=3D"sfrac">=E2=81=A0<span class=3D"tion"><span class=3D"nu=
m">1</span><span class=3D"sr-only">/</span><span class=3D"den">=E2=88=922</=
span></span>=E2=81=A0</span> all represent the same fraction&nbsp;=E2=80=93=
  negative one-half. And because a negative divided by a negative produces =
a positive, <link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:Temp=
lateStyles:r1214402035"><span class=3D"sfrac">=E2=81=A0<span class=3D"tion"=
><span class=3D"num">=E2=88=921</span><span class=3D"sr-only">/</span><span=
 class=3D"den">=E2=88=922</span></span>=E2=81=A0</span> represents positive=
 one-half.
</p><p>In mathematics a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rational_n=
umber" title=3D"Rational number">rational number</a> is a number that can b=
e represented by a fraction of the form <link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline=
-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1214402035"><span class=3D"sfrac">=
=E2=81=A0<span class=3D"tion"><span class=3D"num"><i>a</i></span><span clas=
s=3D"sr-only">/</span><span class=3D"den"><i>b</i></span></span>=E2=81=A0</=
span>, where <i>a</i> and <i>b</i> are integers and <i>b</i> is not zero; t=
he set of all rational numbers is commonly represented by the symbol <span =
class=3D"nowrap">=E2=81=A0<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-=
inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=
=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" altt=
ext=3D"{\displaystyle \mathbb {Q} }">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mi mathvariant=3D"double-struck">Q</mi>
        </mrow>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \mathbb {Q} }=
</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/c5909f0b54e4718fa24d5fd34d54189d24a66e9a" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.671ex; width:1.808ex; height:2.509ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \ma=
thbb {Q} }"></span>=E2=81=A0</span> or <b>Q</b>, which stands for <i><a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quotient" title=3D"Quotient">quotient</a=
></i>. The term <i>fraction</i> and the notation <link rel=3D"mw-deduplicat=
ed-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1214402035"><span class=3D=
"sfrac">=E2=81=A0<span class=3D"tion"><span class=3D"num"><i>a</i></span><s=
pan class=3D"sr-only">/</span><span class=3D"den"><i>b</i></span></span>=E2=
=81=A0</span> can also be used for mathematical expressions that do not rep=
resent a rational number (for example <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-m=
ath-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a=
11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/Ma=
thML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle \textstyle {\frac {\sqrt {2}}{2}}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mstyle displaystyle=3D"false" scriptlevel=3D"0">
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mfrac>
              <msqrt>
                <mn>2</mn>
              </msqrt>
              <mn>2</mn>
            </mfrac>
          </mrow>
        </mstyle>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \textstyle {\=
frac {\sqrt {2}}{2}}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/c1ed29ed3827e5df443031c6a1e01dabc3c7009f" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -1.171ex; width:3.027ex; height:4.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \te=
xtstyle {\frac {\sqrt {2}}{2}}}"></span>), or even do not represent any num=
ber (for example the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rational_frac=
tion" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Rational fraction">rational fraction</=
a> <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"=
mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math=
 xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle \te=
