/a></sup> Outside school, mixed numbers are commonly used for describing me=
asurements, for instance <link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D=
"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1214402035"><span class=3D"sfrac">=E2=81=A02<span =
class=3D"sr-only">+</span><span class=3D"tion"><span class=3D"num">1</span>=
<span class=3D"sr-only">/</span><span class=3D"den">2</span></span>=E2=81=
=A0</span> hours or 5&nbsp;3/16 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/In=
ch" title=3D"Inch">inches</a>, and remain widespread in daily life and in t=
rades, especially in regions that do not use the decimalized <a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metric_system" title=3D"Metric system">metric sy=
stem</a>. However, scientific measurements typically use the metric system,=
 which is based on decimal fractions, and starting from the secondary schoo=
l level, mathematics pedagogy treats every fraction uniformly as a <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rational_number" title=3D"Rational number=
">rational number</a>, the quotient <link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-sty=
le" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1214402035"><span class=3D"sfrac">=E2=
=81=A0<span class=3D"tion"><span class=3D"num"><i>p</i></span><span class=
=3D"sr-only">/</span><span class=3D"den"><i>q</i></span></span>=E2=81=A0</s=
pan> of integers, leaving behind the concepts of <i>improper fraction</i> a=
nd <i>mixed number</i>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-22" class=3D"reference"><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fraction#cite_note-22"><span class=3D"cit=
e-bracket">[</span>20<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Colleg=
e students with years of mathematical training are sometimes confused when =
re-encountering mixed numbers because they are used to the convention that =
juxtaposition in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Algebraic_express=
ion" title=3D"Algebraic expression">algebraic expressions</a> means multipl=
ication.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-23" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Fraction#cite_note-23"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</sp=
an>21<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
