span class=3D"anchor" id=3D"Reduction"></span></h4></div>
<p>Dividing the numerator and denominator of a fraction by the same non-zer=
o number yields an equivalent fraction: if the numerator and the denominato=
r of a fraction are both divisible by a number (called a factor) greater th=
an 1, then the fraction can be reduced to an equivalent fraction with a sma=
ller numerator and a smaller denominator. For example, if both the numerato=
r and the denominator of the fraction <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-m=
ath-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a=
11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/Ma=
