<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id=3D"Adding_unlike_quantities">A=
dding unlike quantities</h4></div>
<p>To add fractions containing unlike quantities (e.g. quarters and thirds)=
, it is necessary to convert all amounts to like quantities. It is easy to =
work out the chosen type of fraction to convert to; simply multiply togethe=
r the two denominators (bottom number) of each fraction. In case of an inte=
ger number apply the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fraction#Reci=
procals_and_the_invisible_denominator">invisible denominator</a> 1.
</p><p>For adding quarters to thirds, both types of fraction are converted =
to twelfths, thus:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e {\frac {1}{4}}+{\frac {1}{3}}=3D{\frac {1\times 3}{4\times 3}}+{\frac {1\=
times 4}{3\times 4}}=3D{\frac {3}{12}}+{\frac {4}{12}}=3D{\frac {7}{12}}.}"=
>
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>1</mn>
            <mn>4</mn>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>1</mn>
            <mn>3</mn>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <mn>1</mn>
              <mo>=C3=97<!-- =C3=97 --></mo>
              <mn>3</mn>
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              <mn>4</mn>
              <mo>=C3=97<!-- =C3=97 --></mo>
              <mn>3</mn>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <mn>1</mn>
              <mo>=C3=97<!-- =C3=97 --></mo>
              <mn>4</mn>
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              <mn>3</mn>
              <mo>=C3=97<!-- =C3=97 --></mo>
              <mn>4</mn>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>3</mn>
            <mn>12</mn>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>4</mn>
            <mn>12</mn>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>7</mn>
            <mn>12</mn>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle {\frac {1}{4}=
}+{\frac {1}{3}}=3D{\frac {1\times 3}{4\times 3}}+{\frac {1\times 4}{3\time=
s 4}}=3D{\frac {3}{12}}+{\frac {4}{12}}=3D{\frac {7}{12}}.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
