-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -1.338ex; width:1.658ex; height:3.676ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle {\t=
frac {5}{6}}}"></span> the single denominators have a common factor 2, and =
therefore, instead of the denominator 24 (4 =C3=97 6), the halved denominat=
or 12 may be used, not only reducing the denominator in the result, but als=
o the factors in the numerator.
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e {\begin{alignedat}{3}{\frac {3}{4}}+{\frac {5}{6}}&amp;=3D{\frac {3\cdot =
6}{4\cdot 6}}+{\frac {4\cdot 5}{4\cdot 6}}=3D{\frac {18}{24}}+{\frac {20}{2=
4}}&amp;&amp;=3D{\frac {19}{12}}\\[10mu]&amp;=3D{\frac {3\cdot 3}{4\cdot 3}=
}+{\frac {2\cdot 5}{2\cdot 6}}=3D{\frac {9}{12}}+{\frac {10}{12}}&amp;&amp;=
=3D{\frac {19}{12}}.\end{alignedat}}}">
  <semantics>
