tfrac {2}{3}}-{\tfrac {1}{2}}=3D{\tfrac {4}{6}}-{\tfrac {3}{6}}=3D{\tfrac {=
1}{6}}.}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>To subtract a mixed number, an extra one can be borrowed from the minuen=
d, for instance
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e 4-2{\tfrac {3}{4}}=3D(4-2-1)+{\bigl (}1-{\tfrac {3}{4}}{\bigr )}=3D1{\tfr=
ac {1}{4}}.}">
