 denominator of the right and is divided out of both. Three is a common fac=
tor of the left denominator and right numerator and is divided out of both.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id=3D"Multiplying_a_fraction_by_a=
_whole_number">Multiplying a fraction by a whole number</h4></div>
<p>Since a whole number can be rewritten as itself divided by 1, normal fra=
ction multiplication rules can still apply. For example,
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e 6\times {\tfrac {3}{4}}=3D{\tfrac {6}{1}}\times {\tfrac {3}{4}}=3D{\tfrac=
 {18}{4}}.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mn>6</mn>
        <mo>=C3=97<!-- =C3=97 --></mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mstyle displaystyle=3D"false" scriptlevel=3D"0">
            <mfrac>
              <mn>3</mn>
              <mn>4</mn>
            </mfrac>
          </mstyle>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mstyle displaystyle=3D"false" scriptlevel=3D"0">
            <mfrac>
              <mn>6</mn>
              <mn>1</mn>
            </mfrac>
          </mstyle>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=C3=97<!-- =C3=97 --></mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mstyle displaystyle=3D"false" scriptlevel=3D"0">
            <mfrac>
              <mn>3</mn>
              <mn>4</mn>
            </mfrac>
          </mstyle>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mstyle displaystyle=3D"false" scriptlevel=3D"0">
            <mfrac>
              <mn>18</mn>
              <mn>4</mn>
            </mfrac>
          </mstyle>
        </mrow>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle 6\times {\tfr=
ac {3}{4}}=3D{\tfrac {6}{1}}\times {\tfrac {3}{4}}=3D{\tfrac {18}{4}}.}</an=
notation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/fa49fddee4338bc2c97bed7f1ec32b937bd7ddcd" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
