times {\tfrac {3}{4}}=3D{\tfrac {6}{1}}\times {\tfrac {3}{4}}=3D{\tfrac {18=
}{4}}.}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>This method works because the fraction 6/1 means six equal parts, each o=
ne of which is a whole.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id=3D"Multiplying_mixed_numbers">=
Multiplying mixed numbers</h4></div>
<p>The product of mixed numbers can be computed by converting each to an im=
proper fraction.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-29" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fraction#cite_note-29"><span class=3D"cite-bracke=
t">[</span>27<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> For example:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e 3\times 2{\frac {3}{4}}=3D{\frac {3}{1}}\times {\frac {2\times 4+3}{4}}=
=3D{\frac {33}{4}}=3D8{\frac {1}{4}}.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mn>3</mn>
        <mo>=C3=97<!-- =C3=97 --></mo>
        <mn>2</mn>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>3</mn>
            <mn>4</mn>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>3</mn>
            <mn>1</mn>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=C3=97<!-- =C3=97 --></mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <mn>2</mn>
              <mo>=C3=97<!-- =C3=97 --></mo>
              <mn>4</mn>
              <mo>+</mo>
              <mn>3</mn>
            </mrow>
            <mn>4</mn>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>33</mn>
            <mn>4</mn>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mn>8</mn>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>1</mn>
            <mn>4</mn>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle 3\times 2{\fr=
ac {3}{4}}=3D{\frac {3}{1}}\times {\frac {2\times 4+3}{4}}=3D{\frac {33}{4}=
}=3D8{\frac {1}{4}}.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/4f8cb5502307bfe7de4971db009e87cf98d14394" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -1.838ex; width:38.271ex; height:5.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle 3\=
times 2{\frac {3}{4}}=3D{\frac {3}{1}}\times {\frac {2\times 4+3}{4}}=3D{\f=
rac {33}{4}}=3D8{\frac {1}{4}}.}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>Alternately, mixed numbers can be treated as sums, and <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FOIL_method" title=3D"FOIL method">multiplied as bi=
nomials</a>. In this example,
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e 3\times 2{\frac {3}{4}}=3D3\times 2+3\times {\frac {3}{4}}=3D6+{\frac {9}=
{4}}=3D8{\frac {1}{4}}.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mn>3</mn>
        <mo>=C3=97<!-- =C3=97 --></mo>
        <mn>2</mn>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>3</mn>
            <mn>4</mn>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mn>3</mn>
        <mo>=C3=97<!-- =C3=97 --></mo>
        <mn>2</mn>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mn>3</mn>
        <mo>=C3=97<!-- =C3=97 --></mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>3</mn>
            <mn>4</mn>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mn>6</mn>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>9</mn>
            <mn>4</mn>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mn>8</mn>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>1</mn>
            <mn>4</mn>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle 3\times 2{\fr=
ac {3}{4}}=3D3\times 2+3\times {\frac {3}{4}}=3D6+{\frac {9}{4}}=3D8{\frac =
{1}{4}}.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
