=3D8{\frac {1}{4}}.}"></span></dd></dl>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Division">Division</h3></di=
v>
<p>To divide a fraction by a whole number, you may either divide the numera=
tor by the number, if it goes evenly into the numerator, or multiply the de=
nominator by the number. For example, <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-m=
ath-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a=
11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/Ma=
thML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle {\tfrac {10}{3}}\div 5}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mstyle displaystyle=3D"false" scriptlevel=3D"0">
