<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Converting_between_fraction=
s_and_decimal_notation">Converting between fractions and decimal notation</=
h3></div>
<p>To change a common fraction to decimal notation, do a long division of t=
he numerator by the denominator (this is idiomatically also phrased as "div=
ide the denominator into the numerator"), and round the result to the desir=
ed precision. For example, to change <link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-st=
yle" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1214402035"><span class=3D"sfrac">=E2=
=81=A0<span class=3D"tion"><span class=3D"num">1</span><span class=3D"sr-on=
ly">/</span><span class=3D"den">4</span></span>=E2=81=A0</span> to a decima=
l expression, divide <span class=3D"nowrap"><span data-sort-value=3D"700010=
0000000000000=E2=99=A0"></span>1</span> by <span class=3D"nowrap"><span dat=
a-sort-value=3D"7000400000000000000=E2=99=A0"></span>4</span> ("<span class=
=3D"nowrap"><span data-sort-value=3D"7000400000000000000=E2=99=A0"></span>4=
</span> into <span class=3D"nowrap"><span data-sort-value=3D"70001000000000=
00000=E2=99=A0"></span>1</span>"), to obtain exactly <span class=3D"nowrap"=
><span data-sort-value=3D"6999250000000000000=E2=99=A0"></span>0.25</span>.=
 To change <link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:Templ=
ateStyles:r1214402035"><span class=3D"sfrac">=E2=81=A0<span class=3D"tion">=
<span class=3D"num">1</span><span class=3D"sr-only">/</span><span class=3D"=
den">3</span></span>=E2=81=A0</span> to a decimal expression, divide <span =
class=3D"nowrap"><span data-sort-value=3D"7000100000000000000=E2=99=A0"></s=
pan>1...</span> by <span class=3D"nowrap"><span data-sort-value=3D"70003000=
00000000000=E2=99=A0"></span>3</span> ("<span class=3D"nowrap"><span data-s=
ort-value=3D"7000300000000000000=E2=99=A0"></span>3</span> into <span class=
=3D"nowrap"><span data-sort-value=3D"7000100000000000000=E2=99=A0"></span>1=
...</span>"), and stop when the desired precision is obtained, e.g., at fou=
r places after the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Decimal_separat=
or" title=3D"Decimal separator">decimal separator</a> (ten-thousandths) as =
<span class=3D"nowrap"><span data-sort-value=3D"6999333300000000000=E2=99=
=A0"></span>0.3333</span>. The fraction <link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline=
-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1214402035"><span class=3D"sfrac">=
=E2=81=A0<span class=3D"tion"><span class=3D"num">1</span><span class=3D"sr=
-only">/</span><span class=3D"den">4</span></span>=E2=81=A0</span> is expre=
ssed exactly with only two digits after the decimal separator, while the fr=
action <link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateS=
tyles:r1214402035"><span class=3D"sfrac">=E2=81=A0<span class=3D"tion"><spa=
n class=3D"num">1</span><span class=3D"sr-only">/</span><span class=3D"den"=
>3</span></span>=E2=81=A0</span> cannot be written exactly as a decimal wit=
h a finite number of digits. A decimal expression can be converted to a fra=
ction by removing the decimal separator, using the result as the numerator,=
 and using <span class=3D"nowrap"><span data-sort-value=3D"7000100000000000=
000=E2=99=A0"></span>1</span> followed by the same number of zeroes as ther=
e are digits to the right of the decimal separator as the denominator. Thus=
, <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"m=
we-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math =
xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle 1.23=
=3D{\tfrac {123}{100}}.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mn>1.23</mn>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mstyle displaystyle=3D"false" scriptlevel=3D"0">
            <mfrac>
              <mn>123</mn>
              <mn>100</mn>
            </mfrac>
          </mstyle>
        </mrow>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
