<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r=
1320445320"><div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">=
Main articles: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nth_root" title=3D"=
Nth root">Nth root</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rationa=
lization_(mathematics)" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Rationalization (mat=
hematics)">Rationalization (mathematics)</a></div>
<p>A fraction may also contain <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nth=
_root" title=3D"Nth root">radicals</a> in the numerator or the denominator.=
 If the denominator contains radicals, it can be helpful to <a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rationalisation_(mathematics)" title=3D"Rationali=
sation (mathematics)">rationalize</a> it (compare <a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/Nth_root#Simplified_form_of_a_radical_expression" title=3D"=
Nth root">Simplified form of a radical expression</a>), especially if furth=
er operations, such as adding or comparing that fraction to another, are to=
 be carried out. It is also more convenient if division is to be done manua=
lly. When the denominator is a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mon=
omial" title=3D"Monomial">monomial</a> square root, it can be rationalized =
by multiplying both the top and the bottom of the fraction by the denominat=
or:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e {\frac {3}{\sqrt {7}}}=3D{\frac {3}{\sqrt {7}}}\cdot {\frac {\sqrt {7}}{\=
sqrt {7}}}=3D{\frac {3{\sqrt {7}}}{7}}.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
