 {7}}}=3D{\frac {3{\sqrt {7}}}{7}}.}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>The process of rationalization of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Binomial_(polynomial)" title=3D"Binomial (polynomial)">binomial</a> deno=
minators involves multiplying the top and the bottom of a fraction by the <=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conjugate_(algebra)" class=3D"mw-re=
direct" title=3D"Conjugate (algebra)">conjugate</a> of the denominator so t=
hat the denominator becomes a rational number. For example:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
