-align: -1.838ex; width:5.484ex; height:5.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle {\f=
rac {3\quad 1}{5\quad 3}}}"></span>".</span><sup id=3D"cite_ref-39" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fraction#cite_note-=
39"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>37<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</=
span></a></sup> The same fractional notation=E2=80=94with the fraction give=
n before the integer<sup id=3D"cite_ref-jeff_37-3" class=3D"reference"><a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fraction#cite_note-jeff-37"><span clas=
s=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>35<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup=
>=E2=80=94appears soon after in the work of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/Leonardo_Fibonacci" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Leonardo Fibon=
acci">Leonardo Fibonacci</a> in the 13th century.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-40" cl=
ass=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fraction#cite_no=
te-40"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>38<span class=3D"cite-bracket">=
]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>In discussing the origins of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/Decimal_fractions" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Decimal fractions">deci=
mal fractions</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dirk_Jan_Struik=
" title=3D"Dirk Jan Struik">Dirk Jan Struik</a> states:<sup id=3D"cite_ref-=
41" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fraction#c=
ite_note-41"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>39<span class=3D"cite-bra=
cket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<blockquote>
<p>The introduction of decimal fractions as a common computational practice=
 can be dated back to the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flemish_=
Region" title=3D"Flemish Region">Flemish</a> pamphlet <i>De Thiende</i>, pu=
blished at <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leiden" title=3D"Leiden=
">Leyden</a> in 1585, together with a French translation, <i>La Disme</i>, =
by the Flemish mathematician <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Simon=
_Stevin" title=3D"Simon Stevin">Simon Stevin</a> (1548=E2=80=931620), then =
settled in the Northern <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Netherland=
s" title=3D"Netherlands">Netherlands</a>. It is true that decimal fractions=
 were used by the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chinese_mathemat=
ics" title=3D"Chinese mathematics">Chinese</a> many centuries before Stevin=
 and that the Persian astronomer <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A=
l-K%C4%81sh%C4%AB" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Al-K=C4=81sh=C4=AB">Al-K=
=C4=81sh=C4=AB</a> used both decimal and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/Sexagesimal" title=3D"Sexagesimal">sexagesimal</a> fractions with gr=
eat ease in his <i>Key to arithmetic</i> (<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/Samarkand" title=3D"Samarkand">Samarkand</a>, early fifteenth centu=
ry).<sup id=3D"cite_ref-42" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/Fraction#cite_note-42"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>4=
0<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
</blockquote>
<p>While the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Persian_people" class=
=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Persian people">Persian</a> mathematician <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jamsh%C4%ABd_al-K%C4%81sh%C4%AB" class=3D=
"mw-redirect" title=3D"Jamsh=C4=ABd al-K=C4=81sh=C4=AB">Jamsh=C4=ABd al-K=
=C4=81sh=C4=AB</a> claimed to have discovered decimal fractions himself in =
the 15th century, J.&nbsp;Lennart Berggren notes that he was mistaken, as d=
ecimal fractions were first used five centuries before him by the <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Baghdad" title=3D"Baghdad">Baghdadi</a> m=
athematician <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abu%27l-Hasan_al-Uqli=
disi" title=3D"Abu'l-Hasan al-Uqlidisi">Abu'l-Hasan al-Uqlidisi</a> as earl=
y as the 10th century.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-43" class=3D"reference"><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fraction#cite_note-43"><span class=3D"cit=
e-bracket">[</span>41<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-45" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Fraction#cite_note-45"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>n 3<span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"In_formal_education">In for=
mal education</h2></div>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Primary_schools">Primary sc=
hools</h3></div>
<p>In <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Primary_school" title=3D"Pri=
mary school">primary schools</a>, fractions have been demonstrated through =
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cuisenaire_rods" title=3D"Cuisenai=
re rods">Cuisenaire rods</a>, Fraction Bars, fraction strips, fraction circ=
les, paper (for folding or cutting), <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Pattern_block" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Pattern block">pattern blo=
cks</a>, pie-shaped pieces, plastic rectangles, grid paper, <a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DDot_paper&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;re=
dlink=3D1" class=3D"new" title=3D"Dot paper (page does not exist)">dot pape=
r</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Geoboard" title=3D"Geoboard=
">geoboards</a>, counters and computer software.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Documents_for_teachers">Doc=
uments for teachers</h3></div>
